## 6. Safety / risk notes
- **Codex write mode is live-fire-untested** (same caveat as the existing "live-fire the codex invoke
  path" fix_plan item). Ship the arg assembly behind unit tests (injectable `CodexCommand`), gate the
  real write path behind the loop's rollback, and mark it for a supervised first run.
- **No infinite fallback:** a single primary├óÔÇáÔÇÖfallback hop, fallback never `codex├óÔÇáÔÇÖcodex`; both exhausted =
  fail-closed stop.
- **Write-phase reset discipline:** read-only judge phases keep the belt-and-braces hard reset; write
  phases must NOT (it would discard the build) ├óÔé¼ÔÇØ the gate + `autoRollbackOnRed` are their safety net.
- **bash 3.2** (macOS) for all `.sh`; new `.ps1` files carry a UTF-8 BOM (PS 5.1); guardrail hook blocks
  literal `rm -rf`/`git reset --hard` in our own commands ├óÔé¼ÔÇØ assemble from parts / `git commit -F`.

## 7. Slices (replace the single fix_plan item; one task per iteration)
1. **Schema + config + tolerant resolver** ├óÔé¼ÔÇØ `{model,fallback}` in both schema files, nested default
   config, `Resolve-PhaseModel`/`phase_model` return both fields and normalize the legacy flat shape +
   `reviewFallback`; unit tests for nested, flat-legacy, and null. *No behavior change yet.*
2. **Usage-limit predicate + generalized codex lib** ├óÔé¼ÔÇØ `Test-UsageLimitError` (+ tests);
   `lib/invoke-codex.*` with a `-Mode read-only|workspace-write` arg; unit tests assert arg assembly for
   both modes via injectable command; keep a `review-codex` shim.
3. **Headless dispatcher: loop implement + periodic review** ├óÔé¼ÔÇØ `Invoke-Phase` wired into the main
   implement call and the periodic reviewer under the new schema; claude├óÔÇáÔÇÖcodex and usage-limit fallback
   both fire; write-phase reset discipline; tests assert the **fallback trigger** with a stub.
4. **Fleet worker cross-vendor + fallback** ├óÔé¼ÔÇØ the same dispatcher in `fleet.ps1/.sh` workers; dry-run +
   stub-fallback tests.
5. **Interactive `/work` orchestrator protocol** ├óÔé¼ÔÇØ encode Option A in the `/work` command + planner/
   generator/reviewer docs; frontmatter semantics documented; doctor already covers the rest.
6. **`/harness-doctor` check 10 + `/harness-init` interview** ├óÔé¼ÔÇØ rewrite check 10 for the new schema
   across surfaces; add the per-phase init pick with recommended defaults.
7. **Docs + prune** ├óÔé¼ÔÇØ AGENT_NOTES learnings, this plan ├óÔÇáÔÇÖ APPROVED, PROGRESS lines, evidence; retire the
   `review-codex` shim once nothing references it.

## 8. Decisions (LOCKED 2026-07-14)
1. **Interactive cross-vendor mechanism ├óÔÇáÔÇÖ Option A.** The `/work` orchestrator dispatches to the codex
   lib via Bash instead of spawning the Claude subagent when a phase routes to codex; frontmatter stays
   the Claude model. (Rejected: B ├óÔé¼ÔÇØ subagent internally shells to codex, indirection; C ├óÔé¼ÔÇØ interactive
   stays Claude-only.)
2. **Schema migration ├óÔÇáÔÇÖ tolerant reader.** Accept both the legacy flat string and the new
   `{model,fallback}`; normalize flat├óÔÇáÔÇÖnested and `reviewFallback`├óÔÇáÔÇÖ`review.fallback` in the resolver, so
   deployed project configs keep working without an immediate rewrite. (the maintainer deferred to
   the recommendation.)
3. **Usage-limit fallback ├óÔÇáÔÇÖ retry once on the fallback** within the same iteration; reset a write-phase
   tree to the iteration base before the retry; both candidates exhausted = fail-closed stop.


